Crooks, the black stable-hand, gets his name from his crooked back. Proud, bitter, and caustically funny, he  is isolated from the other men because of the color of his skin. Despite himself, Crooks becomes fond of Lennie, and though he derisively claims to have seen countless men following empty dreams of buying their own land, he asks Lennie if he can go with them and hoe in the garden.Read anin-depth analysis of Crooks.